Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.53,0:02:19.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0002,,This school is cursed?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.91,0:02:22.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0002,,Yeah! It’s really for reals!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.50,0:02:25.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0002,,The whole school’s talking about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.65,0:02:27.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0002,,I bet it’s just another of those
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.01,0:02:29.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0002,,“Seven Mysteries” every school has.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.37,0:02:32.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Like pianos that play on their own, or stairs that increase in number.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.83,0:02:35.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This isn’t that kind of childish rubbish!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.96,0:02:38.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It happened early one morning last week,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.30,0:02:41.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,when a student went into the art room.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.82,0:02:45.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She was fond of a large painting in the art room,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.12,0:02:47.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and she went to look at it every morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.47,0:02:50.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But then she saw it...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.27,0:02:58.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,All eight plaster figures in the art room were glaring at her!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.81,0:03:01.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think? Mysterious, isn’t it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.36,0:03:03.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was just coincidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.14,0:03:05.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And it isn’t just her!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.86,0:03:10.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don’t there seem to be fewer students at this school lately?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.30,0:03:12.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard there was a cold going around.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.80,0:03:16.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows, maybe they’ve all been cursed by the plaster figures!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.19,0:03:20.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The story I heard is much crazier than those plaster figures!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.64,0:03:24.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You know that gross doll in the nurse’s office?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.64,0:03:26.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, the anatomy model?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.68,0:03:34.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was running super-fast through the hallway four nights ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.35,0:03:35.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That’s dumb.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.95,0:03:39.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Ayumi! Tell him your story, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.26,0:03:41.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? You saw something too, Ayumi-{\i1}chan{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.66,0:03:43.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.24,0:03:47.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyways, we gotta do a Detective Boys investigation
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.48,0:03:49.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,before things get really bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.42,0:03:53.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,K-Kobayashi-{\i1}sensei{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.23,0:03:57.98,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Sumiko Kobayashi (26)\NClass 1-B Homeroom Teacher
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.44,0:03:58.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you can’t behave in my class,\Nthen leave this instant!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.67,0:04:02.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Fukumoto-{\i1}kun{\i0}! Read the next one!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.44,0:04:03.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on! Quit dilly-dallying!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.55,0:04:05.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, ma’am!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.27,0:04:07.10,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What’s your problem, hag?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.03,0:04:11.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Totani-{\i1}sensei{\i0} was so much better.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.99,0:04:16.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There’s nothing we can do.\NShe got married and quit her job.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.25,0:04:19.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is so lame.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.66,0:04:21.75,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Ayumi-{\i1}chan{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.84,0:04:25.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Huh? You saw a strange person?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.85,0:04:29.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. In this classroom, three nights ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.13,0:04:31.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why were you at school at night?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.33,0:04:35.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn’t help it. I was worried about the fishies.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.96,0:04:38.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Fish? You mean them?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.88,0:04:44.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I forgot to feed them that day,\Nso I came to check on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.70,0:04:49.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And then I saw someone in this classroom, in the pitch dark!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.14,0:04:53.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They were wandering around creepy-like,\Nwith a big, white mask on!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.31,0:04:55.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you see their face?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.62,0:05:00.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No. I couldn’t tell by their voice, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.06,0:05:02.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They seemed to be mad, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.62,0:05:04.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn’t you tell this to a teacher?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.74,0:05:09.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I did! I told the assistant principal,\Nhe lives in my neighborhood!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.10,0:05:11.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He promised to look into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.60,0:05:12.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what did he find out?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.40,0:05:18.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That’s just it... He hasn’t come to school yesterday or today!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.59,0:05:23.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kobayashi-{\i1}sensei{\i0} and the other teachers said they haven’t seen him,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.15,0:05:27.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and nobody answered the doorbell\Nwhen I went to his house!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.05,0:05:30.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure he isn’t in bed with a cold?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.14,0:05:33.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He would’ve contacted the school\Nif that were the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.92,0:05:37.44,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}As I recall, he lives alone after his wife passed away...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.82,0:05:41.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Hey, you! What’s all the ruckus?! Get cleaning!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.90,0:05:49.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And you’ll all take Open House notices\Nto your sick friends afterward!{http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Open_house_%28common_school_event%29}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.59,0:05:50.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that clear?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.32,0:05:51.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, ma’am...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.55,0:06:03.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Kobayashi-{\i1}sensei{\i0}! Why the pale face?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.65,0:06:06.40,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Masayuki Ohata (31)\NClass 1-A Homeroom Teacher
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.44,0:06:06.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Dealing with first-graders right off the bat after being transferred here
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.79,0:06:09.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,must be tough, but you should be more easy-going.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.96,0:06:12.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, that isn’t the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.00,0:06:15.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, Ohata-{\i1}sensei{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.40,0:06:18.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.36,0:06:21.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know what’s happened to the assistant principal?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.33,0:06:25.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,U-Uhh... I-I don’t know!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.65,0:06:28.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He’s been absent for two days without notice,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.82,0:06:31.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but I’m sure he’ll show up sooner or later!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.03,0:06:37.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He’s hiding something.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.98,0:06:42.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it! They’re all a bunch of creepy big-shots!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.14,0:06:45.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, now! Do not kick the school building so!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.06,0:06:48.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Principal!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.07,0:06:52.16,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Ryujiro Uematsu (59)\NTeitan Elem. School Principal
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.69,0:06:53.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This school building will already be 30 this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.11,0:06:58.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I’ve shared many hard times with it.\NIt may as well be my double.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.54,0:07:00.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Please be kinder to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.42,0:07:06.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Umm, have you seen the assistant principal?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.02,0:07:13.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Secrets will always get out. He was truly unlucky.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.28,0:07:15.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was fate.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.21,0:07:22.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! Got it, you guys?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.80,0:07:23.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.72,0:07:28.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We, the Detective Boys,\Nwill now break into the school...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.42,0:07:31.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...to solve the many mysteries\Nthat have happened here!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.17,0:07:36.00,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}- I believe this is the one I left unlocked...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.17,0:07:36.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}- But all the windows are closed...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.04,0:07:47.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,- Hey! That’s not fair!\N- Let us in, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.01,0:07:49.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It’s dangerous, so go on home.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.46,0:07:52.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Heave... ho!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.64,0:07:57.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, okay! I’ll let you in!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.24,0:08:02.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Schools at night sure are creepy...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.15,0:08:03.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! My heart’s pounding!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.27,0:08:07.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let’s keep this a secret.\NIf the teachers found out...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.93,0:08:09.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it’s already obvious.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.31,0:08:12.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Especially if you’re wearing muddy shoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.72,0:08:19.68,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Geez. What a nuisance they can be...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.81,0:08:24.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Okay! Let’s go!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.55,0:08:26.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let’s start with the art room!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.90,0:08:38.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yikes! It’s pitch-dark!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.80,0:08:39.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Lights, lights!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.80,0:08:40.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don’t!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.14,0:08:43.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We’ll be spotted if we turn the lights on!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.43,0:08:46.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,At least bring a flashlight for stuff like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.20,0:08:49.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I brought one, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.36,0:08:53.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There they are! The plaster figures!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.02,0:09:03.15,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}There’s a mark where the desk and figure meet...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.15,0:09:06.74,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It looks like Mitsuhiko’s story\Nwasn’t just a rumor.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.85,0:09:11.07,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What’s that? There’s something stuck to the figure’s forehead...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.85,0:09:13.53,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Cellophane tape?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.53,0:09:16.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I don’t think there’s anything here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.21,0:09:19.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then should we check out the nurse’s office next?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.13,0:09:19.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.59,0:09:24.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let’s see... Anatomy model, anatomy model...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.94,0:09:29.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How odd. I don’t see it anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.34,0:09:31.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don’t tell me it’s running through the hallway, like the rumors say!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.45,0:09:37.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ayumi-{\i1}chan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.85,0:09:39.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ayumi!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.75,0:09:43.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ouch...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.56,0:09:48.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay, Ayumi-{\i1}chan{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.27,0:09:49.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.10,0:09:51.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But I dropped my handkerchief somewhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.76,0:09:53.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What’s that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.70,0:09:58.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A doll! I think it came from this box!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.05,0:09:59.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, yeah! Awesome!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.05,0:10:03.79,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}But it’s strange... Why is this out here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.50,0:10:09.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Look! This Tripitaka{Mandelin: Xuanzang} doll has the same name as me!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.48,0:10:10.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And this Sha Wujing has my name!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.24,0:10:13.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Bah. I’m stuck with Zhu Bajie?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.10,0:10:19.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The head’s ripped off!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.05,0:10:20.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It’s not just the head!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.45,0:10:23.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The whole doll is really beat up!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.12,0:10:26.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey! Don’t tell me someone’s out to get me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.22,0:10:28.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It just happens to have your name!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.92,0:10:33.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! It was probably the name of the student using it in the play!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.70,0:10:36.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, not necessarily.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.21,0:10:39.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Look. Edogawa isn’t {\i1}that{\i0} common of a name.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.78,0:10:42.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-Then these are {\i1}our{\i0} names?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.89,0:10:47.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You’re not suggesting this is connected to the drop in students lately?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.00,0:10:51.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,D-Does that mean I’m the next to go?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.17,0:10:56.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It’s not like that! We’re just being misled by the rumors!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.73,0:11:00.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, the plaster figures {\i1}were{\i0} in the art room...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.32,0:11:04.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...and the anatomy model is in the nurse’s office!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.66,0:11:10.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mitsuhiko!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.92,0:11:14.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-The anatomy model is in front of the nurse’s office!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.36,0:11:15.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.62,0:11:20.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?! I don’t see it anywhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.24,0:11:22.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But I really saw it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.04,0:11:26.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Conan! Wait up!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.14,0:11:35.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,See, it’s right there!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.13,0:11:36.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You probably just saw something else!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.88,0:11:41.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No. Look at the base of this anatomy model.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.24,0:11:44.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}“Class 1-B, Ayumi Yoshida”
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.85,0:11:44.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The handkerchief Ayumi-{\i1}chan{\i0} dropped earlier is stuck under it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.33,0:11:50.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, this model moved after we left the nurse’s office.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.59,0:11:53.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then... it moved on its own?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.60,0:11:57.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don’t be stupid. Someone obviously moved it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.52,0:11:59.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But why would someone do that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.65,0:12:01.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don’t tell me they’re trying to scare us!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.45,0:12:06.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If that were the case, they wouldn’t have put it back where it was!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.17,0:12:13.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What a relief that it wasn’t a ghost!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.40,0:12:16.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What’s creepier than a ghost
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.54,0:12:22.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,is the person sneaking around school,\Ndoing odd things at this hour!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.98,0:12:32.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who’s there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.69,0:12:34.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, Conan?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.25,0:12:39.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone was looking this way from the opposite window!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.84,0:12:46.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What? There’s no one there...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.45,0:12:49.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There couldn’t have been anyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.21,0:12:53.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I saw the anatomy model from the window facing the nurse’s office!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.49,0:12:59.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If the intruder heard my scream, quickly put the anatomy model back,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.20,0:13:02.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and then watched through this window,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.10,0:13:05.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,we would’ve bumped into them on our way to the nurse’s office!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.16,0:13:08.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You must’ve been seeing things.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.50,0:13:10.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No. Someone was definitely here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.67,0:13:14.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,See! The window!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.18,0:13:15.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The window?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.10,0:13:16.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,See the white smudge?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.02,0:13:22.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It’s proof that someone was pressed against the window, looking out!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.42,0:13:26.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, we’re in danger all by ourselves!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.35,0:13:28.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let’s get the security guard here!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.89,0:13:30.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let’s see, where is there a phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.68,0:13:34.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! There’s a phone in the staff room!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.56,0:13:38.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.63,0:13:41.19,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Why is the staff room unlocked?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.19,0:13:47.16,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Security Guard
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.46,0:13:49.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He isn’t answering?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.25,0:13:51.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Did something happen?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.12,0:13:54.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, he probably just drank himself to sleep again.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.77,0:13:58.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The guy’s still at it, after all these years.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.65,0:13:59.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After all these years?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.01,0:14:03.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that’s what Ran-{\i1}neechan{\i0} said.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.40,0:14:10.37,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I can’t really tell them I’m actually a graduate of this grade school...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.37,0:14:15.50,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}But now what? Nothing’s happened,\Nso I can’t call the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.85,0:14:24.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}This is the Mouri Detective Agency.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.65,0:14:25.59,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Oh, Uncle?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.16,0:14:31.22,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Oh, Conan! Where are you? Ran was worried sick!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.22,0:14:35.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Teitan Elementary School! Could you come here?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.75,0:14:37.60,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Come to your school?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.17,0:14:42.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Don’t be stupid! I already graduated from elementary school!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.15,0:14:46.07,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}No, I want you and Ran-{\i1}neechan{\i0} to come right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.07,0:14:48.61,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Okay! Roger that!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.95,0:14:52.15,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Why does everyone have to be drunk?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.95,0:14:57.50,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Oh, well. I guess I’ll look around the school more until they come.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.25,0:15:00.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Hey, who was on the phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.26,0:15:03.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.97,0:15:09.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is kind of fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.79,0:15:10.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It is?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.39,0:15:14.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,See? It’s like we’re in a dream!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.45,0:15:18.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What is this smoke?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.25,0:15:22.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,B-Blood!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.99,0:15:27.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It’s not blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.08,0:15:29.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It’s just red paint.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.45,0:15:31.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Paint?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.13,0:15:35.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone’s dripping paint onto the handrail!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.22,0:15:40.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It follows the taped-up paper and flows down the handrail!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.41,0:15:43.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what’s this smoke?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.07,0:15:47.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Dry ice for science experiments,\Nwith water added.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.20,0:15:49.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I found it at the top of the stairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.98,0:15:53.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Meaning the intruder is trying to scare us away?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.67,0:15:56.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! Let’s go up and catch ’em!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.01,0:15:59.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There’s no point. They’ll just get away.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.25,0:16:02.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But if that’s what they want, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.07,0:16:09.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wah! Ghosts! Ghosts! I’m so scared!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.56,0:16:11.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,C’mon, you guys do it, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.79,0:16:14.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I get it! We’re pretending to run away!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.90,0:16:16.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.50,0:16:21.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I've had enough of this!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.31,0:16:29.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey. Can we go out now?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.48,0:16:30.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.21,0:16:36.83,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What’s taking the old guy so long? What’s he doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.92,0:16:41.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.66,0:16:43.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-There are people...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.89,0:16:45.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...in our classroom!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.89,0:16:47.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And it’s not just one or two people!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.09,0:16:48.77,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.21,0:16:53.75,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}There's ten of them! What are they doing in that pitch-dark room?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.75,0:16:56.26,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}So that’s the person Ayumi-{\i1}chan{\i0} saw!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.26,0:16:57.78,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Huh? They’re holding something!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.50,0:17:03.10,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Ah! So that’s what this is!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.10,0:17:05.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Hey, where are you going, Conan?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.98,0:17:08.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn’t it obvious? To catch the intruder!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.79,0:17:15.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this safe?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.13,0:17:18.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Can we really catch them?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.00,0:17:18.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.99,0:17:26.65,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Okay! This is it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.80,0:17:36.86,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Let’s get some light...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.24,0:17:51.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What’s this? That doll from earlier?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.11,0:17:53.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Lots of others are set out!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.55,0:17:56.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There are plaster figures against the wall...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.60,0:17:58.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There’s even an anatomy model...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.62,0:18:00.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What’s that paper?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.95,0:18:01.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,“Parents”?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.27,0:18:04.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This reminds me of an Open House...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.10,0:18:05.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.61,0:18:07.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The intruder used the dolls as students
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.76,0:18:13.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and the figures and anatomy model as parents to practice every night
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.35,0:18:16.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,for next week’s Open House,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.91,0:18:20.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,while wearing a mask to keep from being heard outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.51,0:18:26.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn’t that right, Class 1-B homeroom teacher hiding under the desk...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.29,0:18:29.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...Kobayashi-{\i1}sensei{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.18,0:18:35.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He’s right! Kobayashi-{\i1}sensei{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.06,0:18:44.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then the stories about the moving figures and anatomy model...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.95,0:18:48.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Were because she carried them here every night!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.47,0:18:52.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The running anatomy model was actually her carrying it hurriedly.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.30,0:18:57.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But you should really focus on being nicer to us instead of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.38,0:19:03.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! You should fix your child-hating attitude first!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.04,0:19:05.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it’s just the opposite.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.60,0:19:11.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I actually like you students all so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.80,0:19:17.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I adore my students so much that\NI couldn’t get mad at my last school.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.34,0:19:22.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But at my first Open House,\NI got so nervous that it failed horribly.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.90,0:19:28.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When one boy made fun of me,\Nthe one next to him started a fight
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.60,0:19:30.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and they were both seriously hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.68,0:19:35.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn’t want the same thing to happen at this school,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.13,0:19:39.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so I made myself mean and treated my students strictly.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.88,0:19:44.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But each time an Open House nears,\Nthose memories come back
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.87,0:19:47.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and make it hard for me to handle.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.18,0:19:50.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So I would secretly practice like this every night.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.48,0:19:55.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You seemed a lot like the boy who started the fight, Kojima-{\i1}kun{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.46,0:19:57.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so I was especially worried...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.34,0:19:59.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoops...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.05,0:20:01.92,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}So that’s why only Genta’s doll was beat up.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.30,0:20:06.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}But as a result, the students fear me and call me a hag...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.99,0:20:09.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I’m not cut out to be a teacher...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.89,0:20:13.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That’s not true! I know you’re nice!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.40,0:20:19.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You’re the only one who waters the flowers
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.24,0:20:21.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and changes the fish’s water\Nafter everyone leaves!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.00,0:20:23.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.07,0:20:29.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. None of the other teachers do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.32,0:20:33.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We were all saying how rare it is for a hag to do that...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.49,0:20:38.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Basically, no matter how much you falsify yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.15,0:20:41.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,there’s no fooling children’s eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.18,0:20:45.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Since the truth’s out, maybe you should go back to your real self?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.76,0:20:50.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Though in your case, you might have to fix your nervousness first.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.95,0:20:52.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.90,0:20:57.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But that was mean of you to use smoke and paint to scare us!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.56,0:21:01.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You were the one watching us\Nthrough the window, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.52,0:21:05.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No. This is the first time I saw you kids tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.95,0:21:10.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After I heard your scream,\NI put the anatomy model back
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.28,0:21:14.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and stayed hidden in the nurse’s office for awhile.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.49,0:21:17.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then who unlocked the staff room door?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.84,0:21:20.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The staff room? What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.46,0:21:21.92,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I knew it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.13,0:21:23.45,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}There really was someone!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.32,0:21:26.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Wait! Edogawa-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.63,0:21:30.01,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}There’s someone else, inside the staff room!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.76,0:21:31.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}There you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.79,0:21:34.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A-Assistant Principal?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.81,0:21:40.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What happened to your head?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.58,0:21:42.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,K-Kobayashi-{\i1}sensei{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.78,0:21:50.90,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The person who tried to scare us away\Nwas the assistant principal.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.60,0:21:55.43,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}He came here to find the hairpiece that he lost two days ago
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.43,0:21:59.88,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}when the wind blew it off in the staff room.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.88,0:22:06.26,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Ohata-{\i1}sensei{\i0} created this shocking\Nscene after opening the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.67,0:22:10.48,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}And so the late-night wig-hunt began, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.48,0:22:11.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I can’t find it anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.94,0:22:13.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let’s just forget about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.23,0:22:16.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no! I can’t come to school without it!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.90,0:22:22.25,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}In actuality, the principal might’ve secretly taken it.
